title: Girls Soccer Roundup: Lexington and Ontario win big
text:
Girls Soccer Roundup: Lexington and Ontario win big Staff report 10:56 p.m. EDT October 19, 2015 STK Stock CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Lexington 6, Sandusky Perkins 0 
The Minutemen defeated Sandusky Perkins in a shutout at home in Division II sectional play on Monday. 
Lexingtonâ€™s goals were scored by Lauren Pfizenmayer, Emilee Parker, Brittani Poth, Abigail Adams, Brooke Thompson and Hallee Brown. 
Ontario 13, Sandusky 0 
The Lady Warriors (15-2, 6-0) beat Sandusky at home Monday in a blowout in Division II sectional play. 
Alexis Bise and Brittany McCauley both earned a hat trick for Ontario, Bise also added 2 assists. Taylor Beard and Bria Meisse each scored 2 goals with Meisse adding 2 assists as well; Rachel Miller and Kirstan Franklin scored a goal and assist apiece.
